0A==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native image testing**\\n\\nI can't assume the java executable will be available for native image tests. I wonder if I could use ProcessBuilder in the native image runtime. It seems that the tests should execute properly, but requiring JAVA_HOME might be a hurdle. Also, could we run external Java with the --limit-modules option and classpath? I have to think about the fact that the native image may not include Java, but the environment does have JDK in CI. Keeping the tests focused is probably a good idea!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_k5NTJNsxtyExU49JzsNrXSqJ|fc_0b19892948c3c80e0169efe1677f0c8191b10c78b002541231", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/ant/ant/1.6/*/ant-1.6.jar -c -p org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.compilers.CompilerAdapterFactory | sed -n '1,260p'", "timeout": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3296, "output": 1541, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23269, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777328466219, "responseId": "resp_0b19892948c3c80e0169efe153090c8191b32c9e8001ff8674"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_k5NTJNsxtyExU49JzsNrXSqJ|fc_0b19892948c3c80e0169efe1677f0c8191b10c78b002541231", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compiled from \"CompilerAdapterFactory.java\"\npublic class org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.compilers.CompilerAdapterFactory {\n  private static final java.lang.String MODERN_COMPILER;\n\n  static java.lang.Class class$org$apache$tools$ant$taskdefs$compilers$CompilerAdapterFactory;\n\n  private org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.compilers.CompilerAdapterFactory();\n    Code:\n         0: aload_0\n         1: invokespecial #6                  // Method java/lang/Object.\"<init>\":()V\n         4