apterFactory. This way, I can ensure that the necessary resources are loaded correctly. However, I definitely need to weigh the pros and cons of this approach to see if it fits my needs.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_hE8WTwSmJDbpUXtlwlhtDlZ7|fc_0b19892948c3c80e0169efe22cb8a08191bc0c666b684f2317", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/ant/ant/1.6/*/ant-1.6.jar -c -l -p org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.compilers.CompilerAdapterFactory | sed -n '120,230p'", "timeout": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 10839, "output": 2334, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34677, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777328649950, "responseId": "resp_0b19892948c3c80e0169efe20ae2b4819184daa6320f694b50"}}
